def year(dataset):
    
    print('Overall Pie Chart:')##############################################
    
    labels = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Year'])))
    
    sizes = []
    self_report = []
    for u in labels:
        sizes.append(list(dataset['Year']).count(u))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Year']).count(u))
        
    explode = [0]*len(labels)

    fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize = (20,7), sharex = False)
    ax1[0].pie(sizes, explode = explode, labels = labels, rotatelabels = 90,autopct = '%1.1f%%', shadow=True, startangle=90, radius=3000)
    ax1[0].axis('equal')
    plt.title('Number of incidents per Year')
    #plt.show()
    
    #print('Bar Chart:')##############################################
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    #f, axes = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(25, 7), sharex=True)
    sns.countplot(y="Year",data=dataset ,ax=ax1[1])#.set_xticklabels(labels=["Full-time employed","Part-time employed","Not in the labor force (e.g., retired, homemaker)","Unemployed looking for work","Student","Other","Prefer not to disclose"])
    plt.show()
    
    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(sizes)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/sizes[i])*100,2))+'%')
        
    table = list(zip(labels, sizes, self_report, percentage))
    table = sorted(table, key = lambda x: x[3], reverse=True)
    table.append(('Total',sum(sizes),sum(self_report),'100%'))
        
    #tabulate reference:https://pypi.org/project/tabulate/
    table_print = tabulate(table, headers=['Year','# of incidents', 'Self reported','Self report %'], tablefmt='psql')
    print(table_print)
    
    #self-report graph
    table = pd.DataFrame(table[:-1],columns=['Year','# of incidents','Self reported', 'Self report %'])
    for i in range(len(list(table['Self report %']))):
        table['Self report %'][i] = float(table['Self report %'][i][:-1])
        #table['Year'][i] = int(table['Year'][i])
    table = table.sort_values(by=['Year'])
    
    f, axes = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(18, 3), sharex=True)
    plt.plot(table['Year'],table['Self report %'],marker='o', markerfacecolor='blue', markersize=12, color='skyblue', linewidth=4)
    plt.plot( table['Year'], table['# of incidents'], marker='', color='olive', linewidth=2, linestyle='dashed')
    plt.plot( table['Year'], table['Self reported'],  marker='', color='green', linewidth=2,label = '# of self-reported')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('# of incidents vs. year', fontsize=14)
    plt.xlabel('Year', fontsize=14)
    plt.ylabel('# of incidents', fontsize=14)
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()

#original paper: table xiii and table xiv on page 18
def top_10_root_ca(dataset):
    
    CAs = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Root CA'])))
    
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for ca in CAs:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Root CA']).count(ca))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Root CA']).count(ca))

    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/counts[i])*100,2))+'%')
        
    table = list(zip(CAs, counts, self_report, percentage))
    table = sorted(table, key = lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    table = table[:10]
    table.append(('Sum of Top 10:',sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]), sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10]), 
                  str(round((sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10])/sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]))*100,2))+'%'))
    table.append(('Total',sum(counts),sum(self_report),str(round((sum(self_report)/sum(counts))*100,2))+'%'))
    table_print = tabulate(table, headers=['Root CAs','# of incidents','Self reported', 'Self report %'], tablefmt='psql')
    print(table_print)
    
    #table = pd.DataFrame(table[:-1],columns=['Root CAs','# of incidents','Self reported', 'Self report %'])
    #for i in range(len(list(table['Self report %']))):
    #    table['Self report %'][i] = float(table['Self report %'][i][:-1])
    
    #bar chart
    #sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    #f, axes = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(18, 3), sharex=True)
    #sns.barplot(x="Root CAs", y = "Self report %",data=table)#.set(ylabel = 'Count - Smart Phone scenario',xticklabels=["Deny","Not sure","Allow"])

def top_10_problematic_ca(dataset):
    
    CAs = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Problematic CA'])))
    
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for ca in CAs:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Problematic CA']).count(ca))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Problematic CA']).count(ca))
    
    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/counts[i])*100,2))+'%')
        
    table = list(zip(CAs, counts, self_report, percentage))
    table = sorted(table, key = lambda x: x[3], reverse=True)
    table = table[:10]
    table.append(('Sum of Top 10:',sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]), sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10]), 
                  str(round((sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10])/sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]))*100,2))+'%'))
    table.append(('Total',sum(counts),sum(self_report),str(round((sum(self_report)/sum(counts))*100,2))+'%'))
    table_print = tabulate(table, headers=['Problematic CAs','# of incidents','Self reported', 'Self report %'], tablefmt='psql')
    print(table_print)
    
    #table = pd.DataFrame(table[:-1],columns=['Root CAs','# of incidents','Self reported', 'Self report %'])

#CA self report count
#original paper: fig 5 on page 18
def ca_self_report_trends(dataset):
    CAs = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Root CA'])))
    
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for ca in CAs:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Root CA']).count(ca))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Root CA']).count(ca))
    
    table = list(zip(CAs, counts, self_report))
    table = pd.DataFrame(table, columns = ['Root CA','# of incidents', 'Self reported'])
    diff = []
    for n,s in zip(table['# of incidents'],table['Self reported']):
        diff.append(n-s)
    
    N = table.shape[0]
    ind = np.arange(N)    
    width = 0.35 
    fig = plt.subplots(figsize =(20, 7)) 
    p1 = plt.bar(ind, table['Self reported'], width) 
    p2 = plt.bar(ind, diff, width, bottom = table['Self reported'])
    plt.ylabel('# of incidents') 
    #plt.title('2001 - 2020, self-reported incidents by Root CA') 
    plt.xticks(ind, CAs, rotation = 90) 
    plt.yticks(np.arange(0, 75, 15)) 
    plt.legend((p1[0], p2[0]), ('# of self-reported incidents', '# of incidents')) 

    plt.show() 

print('2001 - 2020, self-reported incidents by Root CA')
ca_self_report_trends(data)
print('2001 - 2018, self-reported incidents by Root CA')
ca_self_report_trends(old_data)
print('2019 - 2020, self-reported incidents by Root CA')
ca_self_report_trends(new_data)

#original paper: #fig 22 on page 22, and table xv on page 23
def self_report_by_year(dataset):
    years = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Year'])))
    
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for y in years:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Year']).count(y))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Year']).count(y))
    
    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/counts[i])*100,2))+'%')
    
    table = list(zip(years, counts, self_report,percentage))
    table.append(('Total',sum(counts),sum(self_report),str(round((sum(self_report)/sum(counts))*100,2))+'%'))
    table_print = tabulate(table, headers=['Year','# of incidents','Self reported', 'Self report %'], tablefmt='psql')
    print(table_print)
    
    table = pd.DataFrame(table[:-1], columns = ['Year','# of incidents', 'Self reported','Self report %'])
    diff = []
    for n,s in zip(table['# of incidents'],table['Self reported']):
        diff.append(n-s)
    #print(table)
        
    N = table.shape[0]
    ind = np.arange(N)    
    width = 0.35 
    fig = plt.subplots(figsize =(20, 7)) 
    p1 = plt.bar(ind, table['Self reported'], width) 
    p2 = plt.bar(ind, diff, width, bottom = table['Self reported'])
    plt.ylabel('# of other incidents') 
    plt.xticks(ind, years) 
    plt.yticks(np.arange(0, 225, 15)) 
    plt.legend((p1[0], p2[0]), ('# of self-reported incidents', '# of incidents'))
    plt.title('2001-2020, self-reported incidents by year')
    plt.show() 

self_report_by_year(data)

#number of incidents by type
#original paper: table x on page 13
def type_of_incidents(dataset):
    Type = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Issue'])))
    
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for t in Type:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Issue']).count(t))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Issue']).count(t))
    
    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/counts[i])*100,2))+'%')
    
    table = list(zip(Type, counts, self_report, percentage))
    table = sorted(table, key = lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    #table = table[:10]
    #table.append(('Sum of Top 10:',sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]), sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10]), 
    #              str(round((sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10])/sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]))*100,2))+'%'))
    table.append(('Total',sum(counts),sum(self_report),str(round((sum(self_report)/sum(counts))*100,2))+'%'))
    table_print = tabulate(table, headers=['Issue','# of \n incidents','Self \n reported', 'Self \n report %'], tablefmt='psql')
    print(table_print)
    
type_of_incidents(data)

#number of incidents by cause
#original paper: table xi on page 14
def type_of_incidents(dataset):
    Type = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Primary Cause (Hilda)'])))
    
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for t in Type:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Primary Cause (Hilda)']).count(t))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Primary Cause (Hilda)']).count(t))
    
    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/counts[i])*100,2))+'%')
    
    table = list(zip(Type, counts, self_report, percentage))
    table = sorted(table, key = lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    #table = table[:10]
    #table.append(('Sum of Top 10:',sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]), sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10]), 
    #              str(round((sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10])/sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]))*100,2))+'%'))
    table.append(('Total',sum(counts),sum(self_report),str(round((sum(self_report)/sum(counts))*100,2))+'%'))
    table_print = tabulate(table, headers=['Cause','# of \n incidents','Self \n reported', 'Self \n report %'], tablefmt='psql')
    print(table_print)

print('2001- April 2020, # of incidents by cause:')
type_of_incidents(data)
print('2001 - 2018, # of incidents by cause:')
type_of_incidents(old_data)
print('2019-2020, # of incidents by cause:')
type_of_incidents(new_data)

#original paper: table xii on page 16
def issue_vs_cause(dataset, title):
    cause = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Primary Cause (Hilda)'])))
    issue = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Issue'])))

    #structure: counts = {issue: {cause: count}}
    counts = {}
    for i in issue:
        counts[i] = {}
        issue_dataset = dataset[dataset['Issue'] == i]
        for c in cause:
            counts[i][c] = list(issue_dataset['Primary Cause (Hilda)']).count(c)
        counts[i]['total'] = issue_dataset['Primary Cause (Hilda)'].shape[0]
    
    df = pd.DataFrame(counts).T
    df = df.sort_values(by=['total'],ascending=False)
    
    print('Table is too big, so I decided to print it as a csv file')
    df.to_csv('Issue_vs_Cause_'+title+'.csv')
    
    print('Below is the Heatmap')
    f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20, 20))
    sns.heatmap(df, annot=True,linewidths=0.5, fmt="d",cmap="YlGnBu")
    

#entire dataset
print('2001-2020, heatmap of issues vs. causes')
issue_vs_cause(data, 'Alldata')

#original paper: tabe xvi on page 23
def issue_by_year(dataset):
    years = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Year'])))
    issue = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Issue'])))

    #structure: counts = {issue: {year: count}}  cause->years
    counts = {}
    for i in issue:
        counts[i] = {}
        issue_dataset = dataset[dataset['Issue'] == i]
        for y in years:
            counts[i][y] = list(issue_dataset['Year']).count(y)
        counts[i]['total'] = issue_dataset['Year'].shape[0]
    
    df = pd.DataFrame(counts).T
    df = df.sort_values(by=['total'],ascending=False)

    print('Table is too big, so I decided to print it as a csv file')
    df.to_csv('Issue_by_Year.csv')
    
    print('Below is the Heatmap')
    f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20, 20))
    sns.heatmap(df, annot=True,linewidths=0.5, fmt="d",cmap="YlGnBu")

#original paper: table xviii on page 26
def rogue_cert_cas(dataset):
    dataset = dataset.loc[dataset['Issue'].isin(['rogue certificate', 'possible issuance of rogue certificates'])]
    
    CAs = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Root CA'])))
    
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for ca in CAs:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Root CA']).count(ca))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Root CA']).count(ca))
    
    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/counts[i])*100,2))+'%')
    
    print('Rogue Certificates, Self-reported rate')
    table = list(zip(CAs, counts, self_report, percentage))
    table = sorted(table, key = lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    #table = table[:10]
    #table.append(('Sum of Top 10:',sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]), sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10]), 
                  #str(round((sum(sorted(self_report,reverse=True)[:10])/sum(sorted(counts,reverse=True)[:10]))*100,2))+'%'))
    table.append(('Total',sum(counts),sum(self_report),str(round((sum(self_report)/sum(counts))*100,2))+'%'))
    table_print = tabulate(table, headers=['Root CA','# of incidents','Self reported', 'Self report %'], tablefmt='psql')
    print(table_print)
    
    print('Causes of rogue certificates') #original paper: table xx on page 26
    cause = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Primary Cause (Hilda)'])))
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for c in cause:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Primary Cause (Hilda)']).count(c))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Primary Cause (Hilda)']).count(c))
    
    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/counts[i])*100,2))+'%')
    
    table = list(zip(cause, counts, self_report, percentage))
    table = sorted(table, key = lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    table.append(('Total',sum(counts),sum(self_report),str(round((sum(self_report)/sum(counts))*100,2))+'%'))
    table_print = tabulate(table, headers=['Causes','# of incidents','Self reported', 'Self report %'], tablefmt='psql')
    print(table_print)

#original paper: table xxi on page 27
def rogue_certs_year_vs_ca(dataset):
    dataset = dataset.loc[dataset['Issue'].isin(['rogue certificate', 'possible issuance of rogue certificates'])]
    
    years = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Year'])))
    CAs = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Root CA'])))

    #structure: counts = {issue: {cause: count}}   issue->ca  ; cause ->year
    counts = {}
    for c in CAs:
        counts[c] = {}
        CA_dataset = dataset[dataset['Root CA'] == c]
        for y in years:
            counts[c][y] = list(CA_dataset['Year']).count(y)
        counts[c]['total'] = CA_dataset['Year'].shape[0]
    
    df = pd.DataFrame(counts).T
    df = df.sort_values(by=['total'],ascending=False)
    print(tabulate(df, headers='keys', tablefmt='psql'))
    print()
    
    print('Below is the Heatmap (numbers indicate the # of rogue certificates/possible rogue certs issued)')
    f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5, 5))
    sns.heatmap(df, annot=True,linewidths=0.5, fmt="d",cmap="YlGnBu")

def non_compliant_issue(dataset):

                                                'non-br-compliant or problematic ocsp responder or crl',
                                                 'non-compliant curve-hash pairs',
                                                 'non-compliant operating procedues identified in audit report'])]
    
    CAs = np.unique(np.array(list(dataset['Root CA'])))
    
    counts = []
    self_report = []
    for ca in CAs:
        counts.append(list(dataset['Root CA']).count(ca))
        self_report.append(list(dataset[dataset['Self reported'] =='Yes']['Root CA']).count(ca))
    
    percentage = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        percentage.append(str(round((self_report[i]/counts[i])*100,2))+'%')

    table = list(zip(CAs, counts, self_report, percentage))

    table.append(('Total',sum(counts),sum(self_report),str(round((sum(self_report)/sum(counts))*100,2))+'%'))
